                    <head>Two Persian translations from Arabic</head>
                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Volume containing a part of the translation of al-Utbi's Tarikh-i
                            Yamani and a chapter of the translation of the Maqamat-i Hariri. </summary>
                        <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh85054797"
                            xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_600B-item1" n="a">
                            <locus from="1v" to="72v">ff. 1v-72v</locus>
                            <author key="viaf_68788612‏">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad Karāmat ʿAlī ibn Ḥayāt
                                    ʿAlī Dihlavī </persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد كرامة علي دهلوي</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="">Tarjumah-i Amīnī </title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa">ترجمهٔ امینی</title>
                            <note>
                                <p>A fragment of a Persian translation of <persName
                                        key="viaf_36806157">al-ʻUtbī</persName>'s <title
                                        key="work_4226">Yamīnī</title>, a history of Amīr Subuktigīn
                                    and Sulṭān Maḥmūd of Ghazni to AH 411/1020–1. It has been
                                    possibly identified with the <title>Tarjumah-i Amīnī</title>, a
                                    literal translation by Muḥammad Karāmat ʿAlī ibn Ḥayāt ʿAlī
                                    Dihlavī, judge of the Faujdārī ʿAdālat at Haydarabad, who
                                    dedicated it to Mahārājah Chandū Lāl (1766-1845). </p>
                                <p>Neither author nor title is mentioned in the text. </p>
                                <p>Incomplete at end. </p>
                            </note>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl>C.A. Storey, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian
                                        Manuscripts in the India Office Library, vol. III</title>,
                                        <ref
                                        target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!8_f047r"
                                        type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/8, ff. 47-50</ref>. </bibl>
                                <bibl>C.A. Storey, <title>Persian Literature: A Bio-bibliographical
                                        Survey</title>, in <title>Storey Online</title><ref
                                        target="https://referenceworks.brillonline.com/entries/storey-online/33-history-of-persia-the-ghaznawids-COM_10203030#V1-0333"
                                        type="n/a">, vol.I #333. </ref>
                                </bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh85080878"
                            xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_600B-item2" n="b">
                            <locus from="73v" to="167v">ff. 73v-167v</locus>
                            <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="">Sharḥ-i Maqāmāt-i Ḥarīrī </title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa">شرح مقامات حریری</title>
                            <note>
                                <p>A translation and commentary by an unnamed translator of the
                                    first 7 <title key="work_21224">Maqāmāt</title> by <persName
                                        key="viaf_9907600">Ḥarīrī</persName>. </p>
                                <p>Neither author nor title is mentioned in the text. </p>
                                <p>Incomplete at end. </p>
                            </note>
                            <filiation>Another copy at Delhi Persian 453C. </filiation>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
                                        the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <ref
                                        target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!29_f003r"
                                        type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/29, f. 3</ref>. </bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                        </msItem>
